    "comment": "Rationale: The meB Splice Insert in Ig Domains of LAR-RPTPs Is Sufficient for SALM3 Binding, whereas meA Is Modulatory.\nSALM3-Dependent Presynaptic Differentiation Requires All Three LAR-RPTPs.\n\n2/3/2018 PIm\n- Adhesion term is supported by cell-adhesion assays in Fig.2 and 3.. Experimental description: Experimental Procedures\n\nConstructs\nThe following constructs have been described: LAR-Ecto-A-B--pDis, PTPσ-Ecto-A-B--pDis, PTPδ-Ecto-A+B+ (Kwon et al., 2010)\n(ref.) The following deletion variants of LAR and LAR-related proteins were also subcloned into pDisplay; full-length ectodomain of human LAR (LAR-Ecto, Y00815, aa 17-1163), LAR-Ig1-3 (aa 35-295), LAR-FN1-8 (aa 309-1078), LAR-FN1-4 (aa 309-700), LAR-FN5-8 (aa 697-1078), LAR-FN1-2 (aa 309-504), LAR-FN3-4 (aa 498-700), LAR-FN1 (aa 309-420), LAR-FN2 (aa 399-520), human PTP-δ-Ecto (NM_002839, aa 21-1174), PTP-δ-FN1-2 (aa 323-518), human PTP-σ-Ecto (NM_130854, aa 30-1167), and PTP-σ-FN1-2 (aa 319-514).",
